    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "Quick comment: it is completely possible, technically, to have a setter that is used (even private ones are auto-detected), and just omit accessor (no public field or getter). It is also possible to add <code>@JsonIgnore</code> on getter, but <code>@JsonProperty</code> on setter, in which case things is not serialized, but can be deserialized."
