      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 3,
      "creation_date" : 1403215816,
      "post_id" : 14859562,
      "comment_id" : 37584945,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "You don&#39;t have to be locked to jackson if you create your own annotation and have it annotated by JsonIgnore and JacksonAnnotationsInside.  That way, if you change serializers, you only have to change your own annotation."
